	<div class="col-sm-10 col-md-10 col-lg-10 post-content" component="post/content">
		<p dir="auto">Btw. if you attempt to register one of the "forbidden" PSMs within your profile driver like so:</p>
<pre><code class="language-c">DevCtx-&gt;Header.ProfileDrvInterface.BthReuseBrb(
        &amp;(DevCtx-&gt;RegisterUnregisterBrb),
        BRB_REGISTER_PSM
    );

brb = (struct _BRB_PSM *)
	&amp;(DevCtx-&gt;RegisterUnregisterBrb);

brb-&gt;Psm = PSM_HID_CONTROL; // LOL, nope

status = BthPS3SendBrbSynchronously(
	DevCtx-&gt;Header.IoTarget,
	DevCtx-&gt;Header.Request,
	(PBRB)brb,
	sizeof(*brb)
);
</code></pre>
<p dir="auto"><em>the system crashes</em> <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/1f606.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--laughing" title=":laughing:" alt="😆" /> no NT_STATUS failure code, you'll be sent straight to hell. So, uh, don't do that <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/1f643.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--upside_down_face" title=":upside_down_face:" alt="🙃" /></p>

	</div>
	
