		<blockquote>
<p dir="auto"><em><strong>Ladies and gentlemen, we got him</strong></em></p>
</blockquote>
<h3><a class="anchor-offset" name="the-ds3-is-connected-to-standard-windows-bluetooth-stack-img-src-https-forums-vigem-org-assets-plugins-nodebb-plugin-emoji-emoji-apple-1f389-png-v-hmq6eelgc4s-class-not-responsive-emoji-emoji-apple-emoji-tada-title-tada-alt"></a>The DS3 is connected to standard Windows Bluetooth Stack <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/1f389.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--tada" title=":tada:" alt="🎉" /></h3>
<p dir="auto">I must be dreaming <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/1f602.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--joy" title=":joy:" alt="😂" /> it actually works, my DS3 is connected to an USB Bluetooth dongle running the standard Windows Bluetooth Stack, the filter and the profile driver! <code>git commit &amp;&amp; git push</code> <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/1f606.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--laughing" title=":laughing:" alt="😆" /></p>
