		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="col-sm-10 col-md-10 col-lg-10 post-content" component="post/content">
		<p dir="auto">Turns out reading from the HID interrupt channel <em>the right way</em> is a bit more challenging than I expected. Unfortunately there's no Bluetooth equivalent of the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/usbcon/how-to-use-the-continous-reader-for-getting-data-from-a-usb-endpoint--umdf-" rel="nofollow ugc">continuous reader</a> for USB pipes in WDF so you've to implement that thing yourself. There are <a href="https://github.com/Microsoft/Windows-driver-samples/blob/6c1981b8504329521343ad00f32daa847fa6083a/bluetooth/bthecho/common/lib/connection.c#L121" rel="nofollow ugc">reference implementations</a> available but they're so "ripped apart" and all over the place I'll instead try to write it from scratch to better understand what's happening. Maybe I get somewhere today, we'll see <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/1f396.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--medal" title=":medal:" alt="🎖" /></p>

	</div>
	
</div>
