		<p dir="auto">Oh, this if funny, I thought I've checked this already but apparently not; it's not possible to have two (or more) USB Bluetooth host dongles active at the same time <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/1f914.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--thinking_face" title=":thinking_face:" alt="🤔" /></p>
<h2><a class="anchor-offset" name="windows-8-1"></a>Windows 8.1</h2>
<p dir="auto"><a class="lightboxlink" href="/assets/uploads/files/1558122907213-e382d185-2c19-4f0e-9fda-8e3d2787c3f8-image.png" data-lightbox="e382d185-2c19-4f0e-9fda-8e3d2787c3f8-image.png"><img class="lightboximage" src="/assets/uploads/files/1558122907213-e382d185-2c19-4f0e-9fda-8e3d2787c3f8-image.png" alt="e382d185-2c19-4f0e-9fda-8e3d2787c3f8-image.png" /></a></p>
<h2><a class="anchor-offset" name="windows-10"></a>Windows 10</h2>
<p dir="auto"><a class="lightboxlink" href="/assets/uploads/files/1558122913175-0f571c51-dfd0-4dfb-b13c-fb727bba3898-image.png" data-lightbox="0f571c51-dfd0-4dfb-b13c-fb727bba3898-image.png"><img class="lightboximage" src="/assets/uploads/files/1558122913175-0f571c51-dfd0-4dfb-b13c-fb727bba3898-image.png" alt="0f571c51-dfd0-4dfb-b13c-fb727bba3898-image.png" /></a></p>
<p dir="auto">Well, that's good to know but hasn't interfered with anything I've implemented today because I wanted to have the capability of storing device-specific settings through a control device anyway. <a href="https://superuser.com/a/1349429" rel="nofollow ugc">So I guess this is true</a> <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/1f605.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--sweat_smile" title=":sweat_smile:" alt="😅" /></p>

