<p dir="auto">As you can see the controller tries for a total of 4 times to connect to the host its programmed to before giving up and shutting off. When I press the PS button again to wake it up within the same session the requests arrive again (and get blocked because patching is disabled in this example) as expected. Good stuff!</p>
<p dir="auto">Now that I know I'm not entirely bonkers it's time to define some IOCTLs for the control channel. And some coffee <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/2615.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--coffee" title=":coffee:" alt="☕" /></p>

