<div class="row post">
	<div class="col-sm-2 col-md-2 col-lg-2 post-author">
		<a href="/user/nefarius">
			
			<img component="user/picture" data-uid="1" class="user-avatar" src="/assets/uploads/profile/1-profileavatar.png" alt="nefarius" itemprop="image" />
			
		</a>
		<div class="author">
			<a href="/user/nefarius">
			nefarius
		</a>
		
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="col-sm-10 col-md-10 col-lg-10 post-content" component="post/content">
		<p dir="auto">Quick intermediate survey result summary after being up slightly over a week:</p>
<p dir="auto"><a class="lightboxlink" href="/assets/uploads/files/1563103144385-1f6fb8bc-4477-40dc-a400-791668ba0ddb-image.png" data-lightbox="1f6fb8bc-4477-40dc-a400-791668ba0ddb-image.png"><img class="lightboximage" src="/assets/uploads/files/1563103144385-1f6fb8bc-4477-40dc-a400-791668ba0ddb-image.png" alt="1f6fb8bc-4477-40dc-a400-791668ba0ddb-image.png" /></a></p>
<p dir="auto">Well, lots of Windows 10 fans it seems <img src="https://forums.vigem.org/assets/plugins/nodebb-plugin-emoji/emoji/apple/1f604.png?v=hmq6eelgc4s" class="not-responsive emoji emoji-apple emoji--smile" title=":smile:" alt="😄" /></p>
<p dir="auto">By the way, another advantage of going with the "ditch legacy OS support completely" option will be: I can develop the function driver (HID-miniport driver, for DI/Unity/PCSX2/... compatibility, pressure exposure etc.) with the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/wdf/overview-of-the-umdf" rel="nofollow ugc">User-Mode Driver Framework</a> which would have loads of advantages (dev speed, debugging, stability, quick release cycles, ...) so that would be another step up in motivation for me.</p>
<p dir="auto">More news to come!</p>

	</div>
	
</div>
